Commentary Text: Tushar Deshpande to Sam Curran, out Caught by Nortje!! Horror start for CSK. Curran bags a three-ball duck. The move of persisting with him at the top doesn't work today. Terrific from Deshpande, gets a wicket in his very first over. Lot of oomph on this short delivery outside off, Curran is hurried by the pace as he looks to pull. Ends up pulling it off the back of the bat and such is the power that it flies to third man. Nortje is perched at the fence, judges it well as he takes the catch first and realizes that he's going over. So, tosses the ball up in the air and comes back in to complete the catch. N.E.A.T. Sam Curran c Nortje b Tushar Deshpande 0(3)

Commentary Text: Dwayne Bravo to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by du Plessis!! Much-needed breakthrough for CSK! Might not be the wicket they wanted but they have broken this threatening partnership. Under the pump, Bravo resorts to his favourite slower ball and although it's a bit fuller, Iyer has clearly not got the desired connection on the stroke. Plenty of height and it's right to Faf at long-on. Just when DC were starting to wrestle away towards a pole position, it's even-stevens again. Commentary Text: Chahar to Rahane, out Caught by Sam Curran!! The catching standard just keeps getting better and better. Sam Curran has pulled off a blinder at backward point.
